      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A few of these ran in the same city race and expected to fight it out. BACIAMI (4) has done little wrong, placing two of three, the latest running on hard to finish third at Eagle Farm. Looks suited by the longer trip and will be winding up strongly. MOMOKA (8) is a two-start maiden who placed on debut at Eagle Farm then was well off best in the same race as BACIAMI. Has upside and may well appreciate getting back up in journey and back to the all-weather. Worth another chance. MOTIVATING (6) ran fourth in the same race as those two and has since finished a well-held seventh on the heavy track at Ipswich. On the quick back-up and can atone on the all-weather. TURBO TORQUE (2) has had plenty of chances but has form on the poly and is among the winning hopes. THRASH A BULLY (7) was placed on the Gold Coast poly two back and can give a sight.",
